## Success criteria

Work through this checklist when you're done:

### Domain 4 — Prompt Engineering & Structured Output
- [ ] `tool_choice` forces the specific tool by name, not `"auto"`
- [ ] `price_mentioned` and `delivery_mentioned` are NOT in the `required` list
- [ ] `issues` defaults to `[]`, not `None`, when no issues are mentioned
- [ ] Retry `error_context` includes: the failed extraction as JSON + a specific description of the mismatch
- [ ] Retry is skipped when `confidence < 0.4` (retrying won't fix a model uncertainty problem)
- [ ] R004 extracts `safety_concern: True` on first attempt

### Domain 5 — Context Management & Reliability
- [ ] `trim_for_context()` drops unused fields before results accumulate
- [ ] Human review queue items include `review_id` (provenance)
- [ ] Human review queue items include `original_text` (human has full context)
- [ ] `reason` field distinguishes between `"low_confidence"`, `"safety_concern"`, and `"both"`
- [ ] `recommended_action` is `"escalate_to_safety_team"` for safety concerns, `"verify_extraction"` for low confidence only
- [ ] No review is silently dropped — every review ends up in either `processed_results` or `human_review_queue`

